Commentary.Commentary: The Proteas have a task in their hand and would hope that their batsmen put up some fight to challenge the Indians. The hosts though would be very happy with the performance of their batsmen and with the pitch deteriorating, the spinners would be hoping to make merry against a lineup which has crumbled so far against so far. Join us for the second innings after Tea at 1500 local (0930 GMT).

South Africa, on the other hand, started well with the ball for a change with Rabada taking early wickets. But the stand of Rahane and Rohit toyed with their bowling and took them apart. None of the bowlers apart from Rabada were good enough to stop the run-flow. The spinners were disappointing, even though, Linde took four wickets but they came a bit too late.

Another Test, another dominating performance by the Indian batsmen. India did not start off well losing three wickets early on which would have given South Africa some hope but Rohit and Rahane nullified all that with some excellent batting. They stitched a partnership of 267 before Rahane fell to George Linde. Sharma went on to score his first double ton and in looking to up the ante,but perished. Jadeja and the rest of the batsmen too had their fun in the middle before Kohli finally decided it was time to call in their batsmen.
Bouncer down the leg side. Nadeem ducks under it. Klaasen goes to his left and does well to pouch the ball. And Kohli calls the two batters back. INDIA DECLARE.
On off again, Shami taps it through point for a single.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Anrich Nortje is into the attack.
BEATEN! Flighted ball around the off stump, Nadeem wants to get into the act and looks to sweep but fails to put any bat on it.
Full delivery outside off, Mohammed Shami pushes it towards the cover region and crosses over for a single. Good running from these two.
Flighted delivery around off, Shami defends it towards the point region. Nadeem wants a single but is sent back by Shami.
The batsman gets a bottom edge of the bat on that one.
Flighted ball outside off, Shami looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards first slip on the bounce. He played it with soft hands and that's why it did not go to hand.
Short ball outside the off stump line, Shami looks to guide this one towards third man but misses it completely.
Shortish length, worked towards mid on for a single.
FOUR BYES! Darts this one way down the leg side. Shami looks to pull but misses. The keeper misses too and the ball races to the fine leg fence.

SIX! Yadav goes but Shami is here and the hammering continues. A flighted ball around middle and leg, Shami dances down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it way over the long on boundary.
On the pads again, Nadeem paddles it fine for a single. First run in Test cricket.
On the pads, blocked.
On the pads, worked towards mid on for a single.
Mohammed Shami is the last man in for the hosts!

OUT! No fastest half century then. End of an entertaining innings nonetheless. A loopy ball this time, Yadav goes for the slog sweep but gets a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards short fine leg. Klaasen calls it mine and pouches it nicely. Yadav departs but some hitting those. Linde has four on his debut.
SIX! Raining sixes! In the slot again, Yadav lines himself up and clobbers it over the long on fence.
Wide outside off, Yadav goes for a massive heave but misses.

SIX! Number 4. Full ball in the slot outside off, Yadav hammers it over the mid off fielder. Nortje there attempts to push the ball back in play but the ball just evades him and goes over him and into the stands.
Fires one outside off, Umesh throws his bat but misses.
SIX! In the slot for Umesh, he hammers it way over the mid-wicket fence. Wow, some hammering.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shahbaz Nadeem, the debutant is the next man in.

OUT! Stumped! A flighted ball outside off which deceives Ashwin as he comes forward to drive. He misses to put any bat on the ball and Klaasen behind the wicket whips the bails off quickly and appeals. The umpire takes it upstairs and the replays shows Ashwin's back foot is not behind which means he has to depart. First wicket for Linde.
Stumping appeal taken upstairs. Here comes the replay, yes, Ashwin's back foot is on the line. So, he has to depart.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Outside off, eased for a single through mid off.
Goes for the slog sweep but misses. It is around middle, Yadav goes for the massive heave but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Piedt starts from round the wicket and bowls it on the pads, Ashwin nudges it behind square to get Yadav on strike. The crowd errupts seeing that.

SIX! This is brilliant from Umesh! Back-to-back sixes for Yadav! Another flighted delivery on middle, the right-hander stands in his crease and lofts this over the long on region for another maximum. Brilliant cricket from Umesh. Declaration coming soon?

SIX! WHOA! Umesh enters the crease with a bang! First ball and a maximum. Flighted delivery on middle, Umesh gets on his front foot and lofts this over the long on region for a maximum. Umesh has shown in domestic cricket that he can bat and he is showing it here.
Umesh Yadav is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja walks! Linde, on his debut gets his third wicket. Flighted delivery outside off with extra bounce on it, Jadeja looks to cut but gets an outside edge which Klaasen manages to hold onto it. Jadeja does not even wait for the umpire's decision and walks back to the pavilion. Not much of a celebration from South Africa.

13TH FIFTY FOR JADEJA IN TESTS! Flighted ball on the pads, Jadeja looks to sweep but it goes off the edge towards the fine leg region for a couple. Jadeja has improved batting in recent times and this is another instance of him showing his class with the bat. Jadeja does his usual celebration of swinging his bat in the air in celebration.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Jadeja pushes it towards the cover region.
Flighted ball outside off, Jadeja rocks on his back foot and guides this towards the third man region for a couple.
FOUR! A full ball on the pads, Ashwin moves a bit across the off stump and sweeps it fine to get his first boundary.
Full toss on the pads, Jadeja pushes it towards long for a single.
Fires one closer to off pole. Jadeja looks to cut but misses.
On middle, Ashwin works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller ball outside off, Ashwin looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards third man. Ashwin gets a couple.
FOUR! Slog sweep to get closer to his half ton. Outside off, Jadeja fetches the ball from there and slog sweeps it left of the long on fielder to get a boundary.
Fuller outside off, Ashwin drives it left of the bowler and takes off for a quick run before the mid off gets to the ball.
Around off, Ashwin keeps it out.
Full outside off, Jadeja drives it firmly wide of the mid off fielder for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Outside off, Ashwin reaches for the ball to punch it through covers for a single.
On middle, Jadeja dives it towards mid on for nothing. Three maidens in a row from Piedt.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On the pads, blocked towards short leg.
Flatter one on the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but misses to get any bat on the ball. The ball hits the pads. A stifled appeal but this was surely going down the leg side.
Around middle and leg, Jadeja pushes it wide of the bowler.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

Around off, Jadeja guides it through point and hares for a couple. The throw comes at the non-striker's end but Linde makes no move to collect the ball, the ball goes to long on and an overthrow is taken.
FOUR! Going down the leg side, Jadeja just helps it fine down the leg side.
Short outside off, Ashwin punches it wide of de Kock at point who dives to get hands on the ball as it goes towards deep mid-wicket. An easy single taken.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Shortish length, pushed off the back foot towards mid-wicket by RJ for a single.
Fuller ball outside off, Jadeja looks to dig it out but misses.
LEG BYE! On the pads again, Jadeja looks to work it down the leg side again but misses. The ball hits the pads and goes towards square leg for a leg bye.
Fullish on the pads, Jadeja looks to run it fine down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, Jadeja keeps it out.
Flatter ball around off, pushed towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads, RJ looks to defend but is hit on the pads.
Full outside off, driven towards mid off for a single.
Fuller ball around the off pole, Jadeja goes for the slog sweep but misses it altogether.
Flighted delivery around off, Jadeja blocks it out off the back foot.
Around the off stump line, Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, it is kept out.
Back of a length ball outside off, Ashwin cuts it towards point and takes a quick run.
First maiden over from Piedt. On off again, RJ looks confused as to drive it or defend but gets a bottom edge and lobs wide of short leg.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off again, Jadeja prods forwards to defend it out.
On off, a solid forward defense from Jadeja
A quicker and a fuller one, pushed towards point.
Fuller ball, driven straight to covers.
Dane Piedt into the attack now. 12-0-82-0 so far.
Shortish length outside off, Ashwin punches it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Fuller on off, pushed towards mid off.
A full ball outside off, Ashwin drives it well but hits the silly point fielder.

DRINKS! The blockathon continued from Saha and Jadeja with runs coming at a very slow pace. Eventually, Linde broke the defense of Saha to send him back to the pavilion. Ashwin has walked in to give Jadeja company now. Let us see if he has arrived with a message for Jadeja.

OUT! BOWLED! Second wicket for Linde! Saha has to depart. Flatter delivery on the middle stump line, Saha looks to defend but it goes between the bat and pad onto the middle stump. Is it too late for South Africa though?
FOUR! Flighted ball on middle, Saha plays a paddle sweep towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, Saha cuts it but straight towards the point fielder.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

FOUR BYES! Good length ball down the leg side, Jadeja looks to flick but misses it. Klaasen also misses it and the ball goes onto the fine leg fence. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that the ball had gone off the glove. Someone from the Protea team asked Umpire Illingworth whether there was bat or glove but he shakes his head.
On a length on off, Jadeja blocks it towards the point region and looks for a single but is sent back by Saha.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja defends it off the back foot towards the off side.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but not given by the umpire. It probably was going down the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja guides it to the third man region for a couple.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full delivery on off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Ravindra defends it out off the front foot.
The batsman drives the ball straight down the ground.
Flighted delivery on middle, Jadeja pushes it towards the point region.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Saha! Ngidi bowls a full delivery outside off, Saha leans forward and drives this through the cover region for a boundary.

On a length on off, Jadeja defends it off the back foot towards cover and calls Saha for a single. Bavuma runs in and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses the stumps. Had he hit, it could have been close.
Leg bye! Full delivery on the pads, Saha looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the fine leg region for a leg bye.
Full delivery around off, Wriddhiman drives this towards cover for nothing.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Saha defends it off the back foot towards the off side.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Saha looks to cut it but does not put any bat on it.
Loopy ball outside off, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it towards cover. It has been slow going for the hosts since the fall of Rohit's wicket.
Full delivery on the middle pole line, Jadeja flicks it towards square leg.
Floated ball outside off, Jadeja looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The South African players put in an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
Flighted delivery outside off, Jadeja pushes it towards the cover region for nothing.
Saha drives this full delivery on off towards covers for a single. 400 up with that run.
Full delivery on middle, Saha defends it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Fullish delivery outside off, Jadeja leaves this ball alone.
Good length delivery on the pads, Saha flicks it towards the fine leg region and take a single.
Low full toss aimed the middle stump, Saha does well to flick it towards the mid-wicket fielder.

Overcast above, breeze picking up, and floodlights on with full effect. Rain around the corner? Hope not but who knows. Will that make Kohli think about the declaration? Doubt he will make any change.
Full delivery on the fourth stump line, Saha lunges forward and drives this to the cover fielder for nothing.
Back of a length delivery on the off stump line, Saha defends this off the back foot towards the cover region.
Good length ball around off, Saha defends this off the back foot towards the cover region.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted delivery around off, Jadeja looks to defend but it hits the inside edge and hits the pads of Jadeja. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.

Full delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Saha looks to paddle sweep this one but it goes off the bat towards square leg for a single. Zubayr Hamza gets to the ball from short leg quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. It wouldn't have mattered as Jadeja was in time.
Loopy delivery outside off with some extra bounce on it, Saha looks to punch it but it goes off the outside edge towards point for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja rocks on his back foot and pushes it towards the cover region.
Fullish delivery outside off, RJ leaves this ball alone to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on off, Ravindra camps on his back foot and defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja looks to work it to the leg side but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards square leg. The batsmen take a couple.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja looks to pull it but fails to put anything on it. It was a poor ball from Nortje and one wonders how Jadeja missed that ball.

Short ball outside off, Jadeja rocks back and punches this off the back foot through the cover region for three. Elgar runs after it and makes an excellent sliding stop. The umpires check whether Dean has touched the ropes but he is fine on that front.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Floated ball on middle, Saha flicks it towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Saha flicks it towards the fine leg region for a couple. Jadeja wants a third but is sent back.
Full delivery on middle, Jadeja flicks it off the front foot past a diving Bavuma at mid on for a single.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Jadeja looks to flick but misses it completely.

DRINKS! Some blockathon from Saha and Jadeja after the wicket of Rohit Sharma. Rohit looked in supreme touch throughout the innings. After getting to his double ton he perished in search of quick runs. After his wicket, South Africans have managed to stop the brisk pace of run scoring. Interesting to see what approach the Indians opt in the next hour.
Full outside off, pushed straight to mid off.
Fuller on off, driven straight to mid off.
On the pads, Saha works it towards mid-wicket and shouts a no as Jadeja wants a run. The fielder there fumbles but Saha again shouts no.
Full around off and middle, punched straight to mid on.
Fuller outside off again, Wriddhiman drives but finds the fielder again.
Fuller around off, driven straight to mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, Jadeja drives it through covers for a couple. The deep point fielder, Nortje was slow to move but eventually got to the ball.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for a quick run.
On off, Saha comes forward and defends it out.
Outside off, Wriddhi makes a leave now.
Around off, Saha blocks.
Good length ball angled into the batter but it is wide outside off, RJ shoulders arms.
Around off, Jadeja runs it through point for a couple.
Good length ball on middle, Saha looks to tap it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge and the ball goes to fine leg for a single.
Around off, Jadeja pushes it towards covers and looks for a run but is sent back by Saha. The fielder there has a shy at the striker's end but misses, eventually concedes an overthrow.
Landed around off, Jadeja defends it out by coming forward.
On the pads, Saha looks to work it around the corner but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters cross for a leg bye.
Anrich Nortje is back into the attack.
Fuller ball again, Jadeja looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle and off, Jadeja comes forward to block it out.
Fuller again, pushed to covers again.
Full around off, driven straight to the cover fielder.
Outside off, Jadeja comes forward to pad the ball away but the ball comes in. However, not enough to hit the pads, goes straight to the keeper.
Loopy ball on middle, tucked behind square leg for a run.
George Linde is back into the attack. He got the wicket of Rahane in the first session.
Good length ball angled away from the batter, Jadeja pushes it towards cover-point.
Outside off this time, Ravindra taps it through covers for a couple of runs.
Outside off, Jadeja blocks it out.
Nice bumper! Closer to the head of Jadeja who drops his hands and let it pass to the keeper.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja drives it towards point where Linde dives to his left to save runs.
Good length ball angled into the batter. Saha looks to tuck it around the corner but the ball comes in sharply to hit the pads.
Outside off, Saha makes another leave.
Another leave as Ngidi bowls it outside off again.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish length ball, Saha stands tall to block.

EDGY FOUR! Through the second slip and gully fielder. Ngidi can't believe his luck. Faf has just two slips for the new man in. Ngidi lands a ball just outside off, Saha throws his bat at the ball with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and flies between the two fielders.
On middle, Jadeja defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish length around body, worked behind square for a single.
Around off, pushed towards point.
On the hips, Saha looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Saha is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rohit holes out in the search of quick runs. Magnificent innings comes to an end. A bouncer on the body of Rohit from Rabada. The extra pace of Rabada means that the ball came quicker on the bat and hit the higher part of the willow. Rohit got in the position to pull, does so but finds Ngidi positioned at fine leg. The South African players shake hands with the Hitman as he slowly goes to the pavilion. He got plenty of runs with that shot but the same has brought his downfall. Nonetheless, a magnificent knock Rohit.
Another ball on the leg stump line, Rohit pulls it for a single towards deep mid-wicket.
Outside off, pushed towards point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

SIX! Time for a few more of those then. Ngidi does not learn as he dishes out another shortish length ball on the hips of Rohit. RS transfers his weight on the back foot and pulls it over the deep mid-wicket fence with ease. Six number six.
On the pads, Rohit keeps it out.

SIX! Maiden double ton. Gets there with a maximum. Just like Virender Sehwag, the man who celebrates his birthday today used to do. The gala time continues for the Hitman. What a series he is having. Got the opening position and he is making it of his own. Gets a good length ball on the hips, he rocks back and hammers a pull over the deep mid-wicket fence to get to the landmark. He got to his century with a six as well.
Another ball outside off, Jadeja makes another leave.
Finally gets closer to the off pole, Jadeja blocks coming forward.
Same ball, same shot, I mean no shot.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja is not interested.
Outside off, luring the batter to go for the drive, RJ leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle, Jadeja comes forward and defends.
Rabada from the other end post Lunch.
Good length ball outside off, Rohit guides it short third man.
Shortish length ball on the body, Rohit tucks it off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
Sprays down the leg side, Rohit goes for the pull but misses as the ball kept a tad bit low.
Closer to the off pole on a good length, Rohit keeps it out. Doesn't look to be in a hurry now.
Around off, Rohit stands tall to block.
On the pads, Rohit flicks but finds the short mid-wicket fielder.
Welcome back! The South Africa players are out in the middle. Rohit Sharma and Ravindra Jadeja walk out as well. Lungi Ngidi to start the proceeding for the Proteas post Lunch, Rohit to face, on 199.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Let's talk about the Protea bowlers then. What to talk? All they have got to show is the hammering they received from the Hitman and Jinx, nothing else. Poor lines, poor length, negative lines as well but nothing has worked for them. Will anything work for them in the second session or will Rohit and Jadeja continue scoring briskly to take the game completely away from the South Africans. Join us for the second session at 1210 local (0640 GMT).

133 runs, 27 overs. Enough for everyone to know who the session belongs to. Just to clear the air regarding that one wicket, that fell after the duo of Rohit and Rahane added another 82 free-flowing runs. Rahane brought up his 11th Test ton, fourth at home before becoming the first Test victim of George Linde. What about his Mumbai mate then? Well, he is on fire! Just a run away from his maiden double ton. He wanted to get to that mark before Lunch and hence there were a couple of chances where one could feel he looked nervous but the Hitman has the luck as well. He got Jadeja for company after the fall of Rahane and has added a quick 50-run stand with him to keep the momentum going and piling on the misery for the Protea bowlers.
Outside off left alone. LUNCH ON DAY 1.

FOUR! Rohit will have to wait to get to his double ton for a while. Good length ball outside off, Jadeja guides it between the slip cordon and the ball races to the third man fence. The boundary brings up the 50-runs stand between the two.

Almost gone! Almost! The Indians in the dressing room do oohs and aahs. Another ball outside off, Rohit looks to defend but gets another inside edge which goes past the stumps. Jadeja hares for another single. Luck favoring Hitman here.
A quick couple and just two away from the milestone. A shortish length ball on middle, Rohit works it towards square leg and hares back for a quick couple.
Closer to the off pole, Rohit this time looks to tap it towards point but gets a bottom edge to the keeper.

Almost chopped on! A full ball outside off, Rohit looks to drive it through covers but the ball takes an inside edge and goes to hit the pads. Could've easily gone on to hit the stumps. Jadeja has a word with Rohit.
On the pads again, Rohit looks to flick but misses. The ball goes towards square leg for a leg bye.
Way down the leg side this time. Jadeja looks to flick. Klaasen dive full length to his right to save runs. A single as Rohit hares for a quick single int he form of a bye.
Good length around off, Jadeja blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball closer to off pole, Rohit taps it through point for a single. A slight fumble there and Jadeja wanted the second run but Rohit sends him back.

FOUR! Nortje is not learning and Rohit is not missing out. Too wide outside off, this time Rohit brings out the cut shot and hammers it to perfection. No chance for anyone to even move. Just 5 away from his first double ton.
FOUR! Another boundary. Runs are coming thick and fast. Nortje starts with a loosener outside off, Rohit just helps it wide of the gully fielder and the ball races to the third man fence.
Nortje is back into the attack.
FOUR! First one for RJ. Rabada bowls a juicy full ball on the pads, Jadeja flicks it uppishly to the fine leg fence.

Short but equally well fielded by Bavuma, surely saved three there. A full ball outside off for Rohit, he creams the cover drive but Bavuma at covers intercepts and makes a half stop. The ball goes towards mid off and a single is taken.
Length ball closer to the off pole this time, Rohit looks to defend it out but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes behind, just over the stumps.
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.
Way outside off, Rohit shoulders arms.
Rabada starts with a full toss ball outside off, Rohit pushes it uppishly towards Temba Bavuma at covers who fumbles and allows a couple..
South Africa have opted for the new ball then. And the one who can utilize it well has been brought back into the attack too.
Outside off, Rohit punches it through covers for a single.
Flatter ball outside off, Jadeja guides it towards point for a run.
Down the leg side this time, Jadeja looks to tickle it fine but misses.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Fuller ball on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
FOUR! Fuller ball outside off, Rohit creams another cover drive to add four more runs to his tally.
On the pads, worked towards mid on for a run.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg and a review is lost for the Proteas. It looked to be a gamble from the Protea skipper. Piedt bowls a flighted ball, Rohit looks to slog sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. Piedt appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Faf after having a discussion opts for the review. Well, that won't help as the ball has pitched outside leg.

DRS TIME! After a long chat with his bowler and keeper, Faf du Plessis has opted for a review. Looked pitching outside leg. Let's see. Never looked like an edge there and the same is confirmed by the Ultra Edge. Here's Ball Tracker, pitching outside leg, not out. Review lost.
Quicker one this time, Jadeja looks to work it on the leg side but the ball goes towards square leg off the inner half of the bat.
On off and middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, tucked towards short mid-wicket.
80 overs done. New ball is available now. Will South Africa opt for it?
On middle, Rohit keeps it out.
Outside off, Rohit comes down the track to defend it out.
Outside off, Jadeja cuts it through covers for a run.
On middle, Jadeja defends it out.
Down the leg side again, Jadeja looks to flick but misses. Another fumble behind the stumps from Klaasen but no runs taken.
Full and on off, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, defended back to the bowler.
On the pads again, worked towards square leg for another single.
Around off and middle this time, Rohit works it towards mid-wicket for an easy run.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Highest score for Rohit in Tests. He is on the charge now. Gets a fuller ball in the slot, Rohit creams it through covers for another boundary.
On the pads, Jadeja looks to push it towards mid-wicket but is hit on the pads. The ball goes towards short mid-wicket and the batters take a run.
Full around off, Jadeja eases it through mid on for an easy run.
On the pads, worked through mid on for a single.
FOUR! Crunched! Linde fires this way outside off. Rohit rocks back and cuts it through point for another boundary.
Around off, Rohit keeps it out.
Outside off, tucked behind square by Jadeja to get off the mark.
Full on the pads, Rohit drives it left of Faf du Plessis at mid on who can't make the stop as the ball goes towards long on for a single.
Around off, Jadeja is behind the line of the delivery to defend.
On middle, RJ lunges forward to defend it out.
On the pads on a fuller length, pushed towards mid-wicket for a run.
What was that? Probably gets a friendly warning from the umpire as well because of the negative line. Piedt fires this way down the leg side. Rohit leaves it alone.
On middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Way down the leg side, Rohit looks to work it down the leg side but misses.
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
A quicker one on middle and leg, Jadeja gets his bat in time to dig it out.
Ravindra Jadeja is the new man in!

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally a wicket. Linde it is, who gets his maiden Test wicket. Linde fires this one just outside off on a good length. Rahane looks to guide it late through the slip region but gets the faintest of edges. Klaasen behind the wicket grabs it nicely. Linde appeals but Rahane is not waiting for the decision as he walks instantly. A top knock from the Mumbai lad comes to an end. First catch for Klaasen in Tests.
On the pads this time, flicked towards mid-wicket for a run.
On off, guided towards gully.
On the pads this time, worked towards leg side for a single now.
FOUR! Wow! Rahane comes down the track again to get to the pitch of this ball outside off and lofts it inside out over extra cover to earn another boundary.
FOUR! Another boundary. This time it is Rahane. He dances down the track, and gets to the pitch of the ball to flick it towards the deep mid-wicket fence.

India were put under pressure by the South African bowlers and they crumbled a bit with the wickets of their in-form batsmen. Rohit, after an edgy start has started to look good and with Rahane for company, they will look to consolidate the innings further. Another exciting session awaits us. Join us at 1210 local (0640 GMT).

Finally, a session which has belonged to the Proteas on Day 1 of this Test series. Their opening bowlers, especially Rabada were brilliant and took three important wickets of Agarwal, Pujara and Kohli. Faf du Plessis would be happy with his bowlers' performance and would hope to maintaining it post the Lunch break.

OUT! LBW! UMPIRE'S CALL!  Nortje has got the big fish as his first Test victim and what a massive wicket it is, Virat Kohli. A length ball which comes in with the angle into the right-hander. The South African team is in a huddle before they take the position on the field. The two Indian openers, Rohit Sharma and Mayank Agarwal come out to the middle as well. Kagiso Rabada will start the proceedings with the ball for the visitors. Mayank Agarwal to take the strike first up.

South Africa (PLAYING XI) - Dean Elgar, Quinton de Kock, Zubayr Hamza (IN FOR THEUNIS DE BRUYNE), Faf du Plessis(C), Temba Bavuma, Heinrich Klaasen(WK, IN FOR AIDEN MARKRAM), George Linde (DEBUT, IN FOR KESHAV MAHARAJ), Dane Piedt, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi (IN FOR VERNON PHILANDER)

India (PLAYING XI) - Mayank Agarwal, Rohit Sharma, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli(C), Ajinkya Rahane, Ravindra Jadeja, Wriddhiman Saha(WK), Ravichandran Ashwin, Shahbaz Nadeem (DEBUT, IN FOR ISHANT SHARMA), Umesh Yadav, Mohammed Shami

Faf du Plessis, the Protea skipper, starts by saying that he is trying everything to win the Toss but believes that maybe it isn't meant to be. On the team composition, Faf points out that, Quinton de Kock is set to open the innings for his side and will try to take the Indian bowlers on, as Rohit Sharma has done for the Indians. Du Plessis further adds that Heinrich Klaasen and George Linde are the two debutants in the side while Lungi Ngidi replaces Vernon Philander.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper opts to bat first. Starts by saying that the pitch will start slowing down from day 2 and hence it is no brainer. The Indian skipper believes there will be sharp spin on offer on this track. Reveals that Ishant makes way for local lad Shahbaz Nadeem. Indian skipper adds that they will have to work hard and they will try to win sessions to win the game.

Toss - The South African skipper is in for the Toss but interestingly, he has Temba Bavuma as a lucky charm for the Toss. Interesting to see if the luck changes for him. Up goes the coin and again it is Kohli who wins the toss as Temba Bavuma calls the wrong side. INDIA OPT TO BAT FIRST.

Pitch Report - Sanjay Manjrekar has Sunil Gavaskar for company for the Pitch Report. The former India legend says that there are plenty of cracks on the first day pitch itself. Gavaskar believes that there will be uneven bounce and hence the batters will have to apply themselves to score runs. Adds that the track will be a spinners' paradise.

It's almost time for the final Test of the series. The results have been the way it was expected but one would've hoped for a better showing from the Proteas. Now, the caravan has moved to Ranchi for the final Test of the series and the South Africans have another chance. What about India then? Well, they are on a roll and would like to keep rolling and whitewash the Saffas to get another 40 points and consolidate their top position in the ICC World Test Championship. Will they look to tinker their side for the final Test, having won the series already? Let's see what is in store for us. Is there some luck in store for skipper Faf du Plessis with respect to the Toss? So, will South Africa be able to present any fight or will India hammer them again to take the series 3-0? Pitch report and Toss update in a while.
Umesh Yadav will share the new ball from the other end.
Now, India have enforced the follow on. Interesting to see how the Protea batters respond in this innings. Can they present any fight or will the Indians roll them out in this innings too?

Indian bowlers, well, they have been mighty impressive throughout the innings. Pacers, spinners, all of them. Shami and Yadav started with a bang on Day 2,then Jadeja and Nadeem took over to the peg the visitors further. Shami chipped in with two wickets too.

Another poor batting performance from the Proteas. Apart from one stand between Hamza and Bavuma, there is nothing to discuss about their batting. Linde and Nortje resisted a bit but their wickets were always on the cards.
Just 56.2 overs to bundle the visitors out and INDIA HAVE ENFORCED THE FOLLOW-ON. A wise decision as there is rain forecast on all the remaining days.

Or will the frustration for the Indians continue? Interesting second half of the second session coming up. The floodlights have taken effect at the stadium. Shahbaz Nadeem will bowl for the hosts.
Good length ball on off, Linde looks to defend but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards the fine leg region for a single.

On the pads, turned towards short leg.
On off, a shortish length too, Nortje rocks back and blocks it off the back foot.
This time he covers the line of this ball to dead-bat it onto the pitch.

Beautiful bowling! Nadeem gives the ball a lot of flight and gets it to turn away from the forward prod of Nortje.
Lands it around middle, Nortje comes forward to block but hits the pad and goes towards the leg side.

Bowls a flighted ball outside off, left alone by Nortje.

Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

OHH! Flighte delivery landing in the rough which spun into the batsman, Linde looks to defend but he misses it and just misses the off stump. Saha does really well to collect that one.
Loopy ball outside off, Nortje defends it towards the point region.
Loopy ball outside off, Linde looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards point for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Linde blocks it out.

SIX! Excellent use of the feet! Flighted ball on off, Linde dances down the track and lofts this over the long on fielder for a maximum.

Flighted ball on middle, Linde defends it back to the bowler.

Back of a length delivery around off angling into the batsman, Nortje looks to fend it away while jumping in the air but it hits him on the elbow and goes towards first slip. Anrich looks is some pain out there and has called for the physio.

OUT! RUN OUT! Bull's eye from Umesh Yadav! Never run on a misfield says Sunil Gavaskar on air. Rabada drives this towards mid off where Umesh slides to make the stop but he misfields. Welcome back for the second session! George Linde and Dane Piedt are making their way out in the middle. The Indian players are out in the middle too. Dane Piedt will be on strike to face Mohammed Shami.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

Now then, 4 more wickets. Can they go past the follow-on total? Or will the Indians roll them out before that and enforce the follow-on? With rain around the corner, Kohli might be thinking about the same. Let's see how things unfold in the afternoon session. Join us at 1210 local (0640 GMT).

120 runs for South Africa in 31 overs. Seems like their session, right? Well, not really, they have lost 4 wickets and are still 368 runs behind. Umesh Yadav struck early to remove the Protea skipper but Zubayr Hamza then was joined by Temba Bavuma and the two added a solid 91 runs between them with Hamza getting to his maiden half ton. And once Jadeja removed Hamza, he along with debutant Shahbaz Nadeem picked a couple of more wickets to peg the visitors further.

We are all set to begin Day 3. Faf du Plessis and Zubayr Hamza make their way out to the middle to face the music. Umesh Yadav will start the proceedings for the hosts. Zubayr Hamza is on strike.

Pitch report - Sanjay Manjrekar is near the pitch, says that the pitch has not changed due to the rain overnight. Says that there might be some explosions off the pitch. He is joined by Sunil Gavaskar who says that the cracks are opening up a bit as the covers have been on and there has been no sunlight. Further says that the cracks has not opened as it was supposed to.

Enoch Nkwe, the South African team director is there for an interview with Shaun Pollock. Nkwe starts by saying that India have played really well and they need to try to make a match out of it but there is no excuse of playing poorly. Further goes on to say that they need to keep putting pressure on India. Adds that they lost early wickets.
The pitch was covered in the morning due to some drizzle in the morning but that has cleared up. The covers have been removed and we will have a start on time.

South Africa have not turned up at all in this Test series and here it is no different. After a good start, they were taken apart by Rohit Sharma and Ajinkya Rahane as India posted a mammoth total. And, when they came to bat, they lost two quick wickets before bad light forced early Stumps on Day 2. Now, for them to stand any chance, their skipper, Faf du Plessis needs to stand up and deliver for his side and hope for some support from the other end as well. India, on the other hand, are in a position of strength at the moment and have the Proteas on the mat.  How long will South Africa survive? Join us in a while to find out.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Now, on both the days, rain arrived in the final session. That can happen on Day 3 too. With rain around the corner on all the three remaining days, the Indians would look to bundle the visitors quickly and think of enforcing a follow-on. The way the Indian bowlers are bowling, that is possible too. What about the remaining South African batters. Faf du Plessis will have to lead from the front if he wants his side to give any fight to the Indians. He will hope to get help from others around him too. Let us see what we have in store on Day 3. Join us at 0930 local (0400 GMT) to find out. Till then, good bye!

Ajinkya Rahane joins Murali Kartik for an interview. He starts by saying that he is happy with his performance. States that him and Rohit wanted to see off the first half hour of the first session. Talking about his ton, Ajinkya says that he was feeling well and wanted to counter-attack post Lunch. Adds that the partnership between the two was very important. On being asked about his cover drives, Rahane points out that his flick between mid-wicket and mid on is his favorite shot. On Rohit opening, he answers that he is very happy for Rohit Sharma as he has taken the opportunity with both hands. On the pitch, Jinx says that the ball kept low early on. Points that if the bowlers can bowl wicket-to-wicket, things won't be easy for the batters. Talking about the two wickets the Indians got, Rahane says that it was amazing to see the pacers get wickets on bouncers.

The South African bowlers looked helpless against Rohit and Rahane. None of them troubled the duo. Once Rohit was dismissed, their bowlers managed to stem the run flow. George Linde got four on debut but not before getting the stick from Umesh Yadav.

What happened before that? Ajinkya Rahane raked up a Test ton at home. Rohit Sharma brought up his maiden double ton. Runs kept coming as Jadeja got to his half ton before getting out. Umesh Yadav came, he hammered Linde for 5 sixes in 8 balls before perishing. Kohli eventually declared the Indian innings for 497 runs.

But not before the Indian bowlers, Shami and Yadav have managed to send the two Saffa openers packing. There could've been more casualties but due to bad light, Kohli had to take the pacers off. And then, after just three more overs, the light deteriorated further and the umpires decided to stop play.
So, like Day 1, the final session has been cut short, due to bad light and a slight drizzle. STUMPS IT IS!

The umpires are having a long chat about the light and they have decided to take the players off the park. Kohli does not look happy while walking out.

FOUR BYES! Poor delivery to start off with by Shami! Bowls a good length ball way down the leg side, Elgar lets it go. Saha dives to his right but does not reach it and the ball goes to fine leg fence.

The hosts, on the other hand, have Bangladesh coming to play a series, IF THE ISSUES BETWEEN THE PLAYERS AND BOARD RESOLVE. That series is set to begin on November 3, 2019 with the first T20I to be played in Delhi. We will love to have your company for that game. Till then Happy Diwali in advance. TAKE CARE!
That's it from this Test series then. The visitors from here play England at home on Boxing day. Interesting to see if they can recover from this hammering from the Indians by then.

The winning skipper, Virat Kohli terms the win as an amazing one. States that the bowlers are taking the wickets without having had to rely on the surface. Believes great mindset helps them perform like that. Adds that he is proud of the team. Says that seeing the pacers steaming in, spinners bowling consistently feels good. Kohli says that to be the best side in the world, they knew that they need to be multi-dimensional. Adds that it's all about team efforts. Points that the side does not mind playing an extra bowler instead of playing an extra batsman. Adds that the side has great belief and that they can win anywhere in the world. States that the side wants to be the best side in the world.

ROHIT SHARMA IS THE MAN OF THE MATCH AS WELL AS MAN OF THE SERIES. The new Indian Test opener starts by saying that he is thankful for getting the opportunity at the top. States that he will take a lot of confidence from the series as an opener. Adds that it's a great start for him and he would love to carry on. Further says that when he started opening in 2013 in ODIs, he realized that the opener needs to show some discipline early on. Believes that the management, the coach and the skipper supported him well and that's what helps the player do better. Points that he backs himself for getting those big scores.

The South African skipper, Faf du Plessis starts by saying that the frustrating part for them was that they started well with the bat in the first innings of the first Test but things went downward from there. Congratulates the Indians for dominating all the three Tests. On the Indian bowling attack, the Protea skipper says that in 2015, there were spinning tracks but this time around things are different. Adds that the pitches are perfect for Test cricket. Credits the Indian bowlers for being relentless. Says that the Indian seamers bowled a stump-to-stump line and that's why they were successful. Believes that the South Africans were not able to do that consistently. On positives from the tour, Faf says that a lot of young players are coming in. Adds that the series has been tough for them but they will try to compete next time. Adds that touring India has always been tough and the stats speak for themselves.

Ravi Shastri is there for the interview. Shastri says that the bowling has improved so much that they have taken the pitch out of the equation. Says that their batting is so good that they focus on the 20 wickets along with points. On Rohit Sharma and Rahane, Ravi says that Rahane was not going anywhere from the middle order and he just needed to rediscover his touch. Adds that Rohit did phenomenally well as an opener. He knew when to leave the ball, when to defend and when to attack. On Shahbaz Nadeem, Shastri says that he is very impressed with him and says that the first wicket he got was a spinner's delight. Further says that even he in his prime was not able to do what Nadeem did. Says that it is a team effort and there are 6 to 7 players who will put their hand up and contribute for the team.

Mohammed Shami and Mayank Agarwal are in for a chat with Manjrekar. Shami says that the pacers are always ready with the responsibility. Adds that the Indian skipper gives them a lot of confidence by allowing them to have fielders wherever they want to. Tells that they try to put the balls in good lines and lengths. Shami says that everyone works hard on their fitness and that has helped them. He further adds that they have been born and brought up in these conditions so that makes things easier for them. States that everyone in the team enjoys each other's success. Agarwal adds that he was happy to get a debut in Australia. Credits the bowlers for picking 20 wickets in almost every game. On the Protea batters struggling against the Indian quicks, Agarwal says that he enjoys the sight of the opposition batters hopping to play the Indian bowlers.

Let's rewind the series then. It was all about Rohit Sharma and Mayank Agarwal in the first Test. Dean Elgar and Quinton de Kock scored centuries but that was it. After another ton from Rohit Sharma, the Indian bowlers bundled the visitors for a mere 191 runs to win the Test by 203 runs. Ravichandran Ashwin got a 7-fer in the first innings and Shami got a fifer in the second. In the second Test, it was time for a Virat Kohli show as he raked up a double ton while Agarwal scored back-to-back Test match centuries. With contributions from Pujara, Rahane and Jadeja, India yet again posted a huge total of 601 runs before the declaration. And then the Indian bowlers took the responsibility upon them and once again bundled the South Africans for 275 runs which could've been lot less if not for the 109-run stand between Maharaj and Philander for the 9th wicket. Indian skipper Kohli enforced the follow-on there too and the bowlers this time combined together to bundle the visitors out for 189 runs and winning the game by an innings and 137 runs. We already know what has happened here in the final game.

Second innings' Shami was at it again as he picked up 3 wickets while Yadav picked up 2. Jadeja and Ashwin had one wicket to their name too. Nadeem came to bowl the second over of the morning session of Day 4 and picked up the two wickets to seal the game to complete the whitewash.

Then again, it was all about the Indian bowling. The top order collapsed, Dean Elgar had to retire hurt after getting hit on the helmet with Theunis de Bruyn becoming the first-ever concussion substitute for the South Africans. George Linde and Dane Piedt frustrated the Indians with a brief stand but they eventually got out. De Bruyn along with Nortje made sure that the game goes to Day 4. But eventually India took just 12 balls to wrap up the things.

Then came the Indian bowling. Two pacers bouncing the openers out before bad weather interrupted the second day's play. Day 3 started with Umesh Yadav removing the visitors' skipper Faf du Plessis in the first over. Then, a 91-run stand was the only positive that happened for the Proteas in the first innings. Hamza after getting to his maiden half ton departed and the visitors were bundled for a paltry total of 162 runs. Umesh Yadav was the pick of the bowlers with 3 scalps while Shami, Jadeja and debutant Nadeem picked two apiece. Kohli then enforced the follow-on, 8th time as a captain, most by an Indian.

The bowling for the Proteas started with a positive note with Rabada and Ngidi troubling the Indians at the top. But once Rohit and Rahane got their eyes in, they hammered all the Protea bowlers. After the early wickets, the Protea bowlers looked listless. Debutant George Linde got 4 wickets to his name but not before giving away 133 runs in 31 overs.

Let's talk about how the Test started. Faf du Plessis, the Protea skipper arrived for the toss with Temba Bavuma for some luck. Well, no luck as Kohli won the toss and opted to bat first. The decision looked to backfire when Rabada struck twice to leave India reeling at 39/3. And then two Mumbai lads got together and stitched a mammoth 267-run stand between them. Rohit Sharma went on to score his maiden double ton while Rahane got to a century at home after 3 years. Ravindra Jadeja scored a half ton too but Umesh Yadav's 5 sixes in 10 balls added insult to injury for the Proteas and helped India post 497 runs before Virat declared the innings.

Bruised! Whitewashed! Beaten! Clinical! Dominant! Unbeaten! The first three words describe the Proteas' Test series and the last three describe the way the Indians have played. Another 40 points for India in the ICC World Test Championship as they consolidate their position further at the top (240 points). A big zero in front of the name of the visitors in the same points table, after playing 3 games.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! India finish the game off in just two overs to end the series with a whitewash and it has happened in an unusual manner. Full delivery on off, Ngidi drives this towards the mid on region but it hits Nortje flush on the wrists and lobs up in the air. Nadeem catches it off the rebound and it is given out. Nortje looks in serious pain out there. The Indian players check on him whether he is fine or not. INDIA WIN THE MATCH BY AN INNINGS AND 202 RUNS.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

Flatter delivery outside off which kept very low, Theunis looks to cut this one but it goes off the bottom edge towards Saha. He bends down and takes an excellent catch. The umpire gives it out immediately. One more wicket to go for the Indians to wrap up the series.

Mohammed Shami to start the proceedings for the hosts, de Bruyn to face him first up. Wriddhiman Saha is back for the wicketkeeping duties after suffering an injury on his hand on Day 3. Here we go.
Weather report - It is a perfect day to play cricket as it is bright and sunny at the moment.

Pitch report - Sunil Gavaskar is there near the pitch. He says that the cracks have opened up a little but that will not affect the game. Further says that the South African batters were looking to get to the pitch of the ball but were getting out between bat and pad. Further says that the Protea bowlers were bowling too short. Adds that the Indian bowlers have been so good that they have not been able to cope with it.

2 deliveries? 20 deliveries? 200 deliveries? How long Day 4 will last? Any chance for a South African redemption? Doesn't look like that way? Then, any possibility of a draw? Yes, the two batters at the crease dig in, play and play and keep playing. And then rain to their rescue. Anything is possible in cricket. What will happen? We will find out soon. Welcome to our coverage of Day 4.
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

Now, just two more wickets. How long will the Indians take to get them? Can the remaining two wickets frustrate the Indians? We will have the answers on Day 4. Join us for that at 0930 local (0400 GMT).

Murali Kartik has got debutant Shahbaz Nadeem for an interview. He says that it is nice to make a debut on his home ground after years of hard work in the domestic circuit. On receiving the Test cap, says that he was excited and emotional on getting the cap. Further goes on to say, that when the match started, he started focusing more on the match and how to bowl on this wicket. On his first wicket, Nadeem points out that it was a typical wicket for a left-arm spinner as he deceived Bavuma with the flight. Adds that he enjoys playing with Ashwin and Jadeja as he gets to learn a lot from them. Adds that till the ball was hard, there was a bit for the spinners but once the ball gets old, it becomes easier for the batsmen.

In the bowling department for the Indians, it was the second innings specialist, Mohammed Shami who was at it again as he picked up three wickets. He got good support from Umesh Yadav who got two. Jadeja picked up two as well while Ashwin finally got one in the match too.

The start in the second innings for the Proteas was same as the first. The Indian pacers demolished the top order of the visitors to leave them tattering at 36 for 5. Dean Elgar was hit on the helmet by a bouncer off Umesh Yadav and we had a concussion substitute as de Bruyn replaced Elgar for the second innings. George Linde and Dane Piedt once again troubled the Indians for a while but they eventually fell.

It was all about the Indian bowlers in the morning session as they pegged the Protea innings with regular wickets. Umesh Yadav picked up three while Shami, Nadeem and Jadeja got two wickets in bundling out the visitors.

The day started with Umesh Yadav picking up an early wicket in the morning. Hamza and Bavuma stitched a decent partnership but once that stand was broken, the South African innings fell apart. Linde along with Nortje frustrated the Indian bowlers for a while but the hosts eventually bundled them out and enforced a follow-on. This is the 8th time that Virat Kohli has enforced the follow-on, most by an Indian captain.

So the light is fading further, the umpire takes the bails off and we are off. STUMPS ON DAY 3. 16 wickets. One would think that India have batted too. Well, not really. All of the wickets fell are of the visitors. 8 of the first innings and 8 in the second. No challenge from the Protea batters in the final innings of the Test series. Just two more wickets for the Indians to complete a whitewash.

The visitors, on the other hand, were dismal with the bat. They had no clue as to how to play the swinging deliveries of the Indian pace bowlers and are now staring at an innings defeat. Will this match go to Day 4 or will it finish today itself? Join us in 1455 local (0925 GMT)

What a session this has been for India! They bowled out South Africa for a paltry total and made South Africa bat again. Then, Umesh and Shami came out with venom and prized out four quick wickets. They are just six wickets away from an innings victory and this match looks likely to finish on Day 3 itself.
